#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:1
msgid "Use and publish packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:3
msgid ""
"MoonBit's build system seamlessly integrates package management and "
"documentation  generation tools, allowing users to easily fetch "
"dependencies from [mooncakes.io](https://mooncakes.io),  access module "
"documentation, and publish new modules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:7
msgid ""
"Before getting started, make sure you have installed "
"[moon](https://www.moonbitlang.com/download/)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:9
msgid "Setup mooncakes.io account"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:12
msgid "If you don't want to publish, you can skip this step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:15
msgid ""
"If you don't have an account on mooncakes.io, run `moon register` and "
"follow the  guide. If you have previously registered an account, you can "
"use `moon login` to log in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:18
msgid ""
"When you see the following message, it means you have successfully logged"
" in:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:20
msgid "API token saved to ~/.moon/credentials.json\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:24
msgid "Setup MoonBit project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:26
msgid ""
"Open an existing project or create a new project via `moon new <PATH>`. "
"For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:28
msgid ""
"$ moon new .\n"
"Created username/myapp at .\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:33
msgid "It will generate template files in the path:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:35
msgid ""
"├── AGENTS.md                    # Collaboration guide for agents\n"
"├── LICENSE                      # Open-source license \n"
"├── README.mbt.md                # README file with type checking support"
" for moonbit \n"
"├── README.md -> README.mbt.md   # Symlink for platforms that expect "
"README.md\n"
"├── cmd                           \n"
"│   └── main                     \n"
"│       ├── main.mbt             # MoonBit source file \n"
"│       └── moon.pkg             # Package configuration for "
"username/myapp/cmd/main package\n"
"├── moon.mod.json                # Module configuration for "
"username/myapp module\n"
"├── moon.pkg                     # Package configuration for "
"username/myapp package\n"
"├── myapp.mbt                    # MoonBit source file\n"
"├── myapp_test.mbt               # Black-box test\n"
"└── myapp_wbtest.mbt             # White-box test\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:51
msgid ""
"`moon new <PATH>` generates a starter module with two packages. A module "
"is a  publishing unit that contains multiple packages. A package "
"represents a namespace  and a compilation unit, is defined by a package "
"configuration file, and includes  the `.mbt` files in the same directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:56
msgid ""
"Modules and packages are identified by a special path (not the file path "
"in the file system). For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:59
msgid ""
"username/myapp/cmd/main\n"
"─────────────────┬─────\n"
"────────┬─────   │\n"
"        │        │\n"
"        │        └─ package `username/myapp/cmd/main` within the "
"`username/myapp` module\n"
"        │\n"
"        └────────── module path. It also defines the package "
"`username/myapp`\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:69
msgid ""
"The template contains test files, documentation, and collaboration "
"metadata by default.  You can safely remove any template files you do not"
" need.  The following is also a valid MoonBit project:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:73
msgid ""
"├── moon.mod.json\n"
"├── moon.pkg\n"
"└── source.mbt\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:79
msgid "Add dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:81
msgid ""
"You can browse all available modules on "
"[mooncakes.io](https://mooncakes.io). Use `moon add` to add the "
"dependencies you need, or manually edit the `deps` field in "
"`moon.mod.json`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:85
msgid ""
"For example, to add the latest version of the [moonbit-"
"community/starter](https://mooncakes.io/docs/moonbit-community/starter) "
"module:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:87
msgid "$ moon add moonbit-community/starter\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:92
msgid ""
"Moon also supports local dependencies. See [Dependency "
"Management](/toolchain/moon/module.md#dependency-management) for more "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:95
msgid "Import packages from module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:97
msgid ""
"The `moonbit-community/starter` module contains a `moonbit-"
"community/starter/rabbit` package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:99
msgid ""
"After adding the [moonbit-community/starter](https://mooncakes.io/docs"
"/moonbit-community/starter) module to your dependencies, to use the "
"`moonbit-community/starter/rabbit` package in the "
"`username/myapp/cmd/main` package, you need to import the package first:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:101
msgid ""
"// add this import to `cmd/main/moon.pkg`\n"
"import {\n"
"  \"moonbit-community/starter/rabbit\"\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"options(\n"
"  \"is-main\": true\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:113
msgid "You can also give an alias to the imported package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:115
msgid ""
"import {\n"
"  \"moonbit-community/starter/rabbit\" @alias\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:122
msgid "Now you can call the function `hello` in `rabbit` package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:124
msgid ""
"// in `cmd/main/main.mbt`\n"
"fn main {\n"
"  // println(\"hello\")\n"
"  @rabbit.hello()\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:132
msgid "Run your main package and see what happens in the terminal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:134
msgid "$ moon run cmd/main\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:138
msgid "Remove dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:140
msgid "You can remove dependencies via `moon remove <module name>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:142
msgid "Publish your module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:144
msgid ""
"If you are ready to share your module, use `moon publish` to push a "
"module to mooncakes.io. There are some important considerations to keep "
"in mind before publishing:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:147
msgid "Semantic versioning convention"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:149
msgid ""
"MoonBit's package management follows the convention of [Semantic "
"Versioning](https://semver.org/). Each module must define a version "
"number in the format `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`. With each push, the module must"
" increment the:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:151
msgid "MAJOR version when you make incompatible API changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:152
msgid "MINOR version when you add functionality in a backward compatible manner"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:153
msgid "PATCH version when you make backward compatible bug fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:155
msgid ""
"Additional labels for pre-release and build metadata are available as "
"extensions to the `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH` format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:157
msgid ""
"moon implements the [minimal version "
"selection](https://research.swtch.com/vgo-mvs), which automatically "
"handles and installs dependencies based on the module's semantic "
"versioning information. Minimal version selection assumes that each "
"module declares its own dependency requirements and follows semantic "
"versioning convention, aiming to make the user's dependency graph as "
"close as possible to the author's development-time dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:159
msgid "Readme & metadata"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:161
msgid "Metadata in `moon.mod.json` and `README.md` will be shown in mooncakes.io."
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:163
msgid "Metadata consist of the following sections:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:165
msgid ""
"`license`: license of this module, it following the "
"[SPDX](https://spdx.dev/about/overview/) convention"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:166
msgid "`keywords`: keywords of this module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:167
msgid "`repository`: URL of the package source repository"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:168
msgid "`description`: short description to this module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../toolchain/moon/package-manage-tour.md:169
msgid "`homepage`: URL of the module homepage"
msgstr ""

